  "summary": "MediaWiki is a monolithic PHP 8.3 wiki application served via Apache HTTP Server (reverse proxy) → PHP-FPM, exposing three HTTP entry points: the classic page-rendering frontend (index.php), the Action API (api.php), and a modern REST API (rest.php). All tiers share a pluggable persistence layer composed of a relational database (MySQL/MariaDB/PostgreSQL/SQLite via Wikimedia RDBMS), a key-value object cache (Memcached, Redis, or APCu via BagOStuff/WANObjectCache), a DB- or Redis-backed asynchronous job queue, and a pluggable FileBackend for media storage. Supporting services include SMTP email delivery (PEAR Mail), StatsD metrics emission, outbound HTTP via GuzzleHTTP, and a CLI maintenance subsystem; the entire application is extensible through a HookContainer-based extension/skin API.",
